\frac{\sin \pi x}{\pi x}=\prod_{n=1}^{\infty}\left(1-\frac{x^2}{n^2}\right)
\sin(x)
 \frac{\pi \cot(\pi x)}{x} = \sum_{n=-\infty}^{\infty}\frac{1}{x^2-n^2} \quad x\neq \mathbb{Z}
 \implies \frac{\pi \cot(\pi x)}{x}= \frac{1}{x^2}+2\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{x^2-n^2}
 \implies {\pi \cot(\pi x)}= \frac{1}{x}+2\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{x}{x^2-n^2}. 
x
